Program: Discovery
Title: Gamma Rays
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwws
Last Broadcast Date: 19 May 1997
Gamma ray bursts, what they are and what they can tell us. Also in the programme life as interpreted by physics, the limits of reductionism in biology and what happened in Aristotle's brain when he looked at a waterfall. Presenter: Martin Redfern.